We recommend that the Municipal Mayor enjoin the:

a. Municipal Engineer to submit monthly, aside from the list of building permits issued, the list of persons/ establishments issued with certificates of occupancy/ installation for assessment purposes and maintain records of issuances thereof, and;

b. Municipal Assessor to conduct inspection and assessment within a reasonable period of time. And, submit to MEO a list of real properties found during its ocular inspections without corresponding building and/or occupancy permits.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the Municipal Treasurer to:

Submit the collector’s RCDs pertaining to their CY 2021 collections for further verification;

Enjoin the AOs to prepare and submit timely their Monthly RAAF and attach such report to Monthly CRAAF;

Prepare and submit RCDs in prescribed form; and

Submit the CRAAF within the prescribed period.

Recommendations:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor enjoin the:
Municipal Accountant to provide adjusting journal entry for the undelivered goods by debiting the Accounts Payable account amounting to P514,687.00;
Municipal Accountant to exert effort to locate the supporting documents to prove the validity of the claims and to enforce payment thereof.  Communicate, in writing, to the concerned departments to determine if such payables are still valid. If found to be no longer payable or without valid claimants which are two-year-old or over and/or other undocumented accounts payable irrespective of age, it should be reverted to unappropriated surplus and funds can be used to finance various projects and programs;
Require that obligations shall be covered with the required documents such as Purchase Orders, Delivery Receipts, Sales Charge Invoice, Obligation Requests, Acceptance and Inspection Reports among others, to serve as basis for recording; and
Retain copies of supporting documents for all accounts payable recorded.

Recommendations:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the:
Municipal Treasurer and other officials concerned to undertake effective, efficient, and aggressive tax collection strategies to improve collection. Prepare and serve NDs for all delinquent RPUs, prioritize those which are more than 10 years delinquent. If possible, coordinate with other offices that are regularly conducting field inspections, to help them in the distribution of NDs;
Municipal Assessor to review the assessment rolls as it appears that several RPUs under the Republic of the Philippines were still assessed and computed with tax due. Coordinate with the Provincial Assessor on correcting the said records in the ETRACS;
Municipal Treasurer to conduct dialogue with the owners of the RPUs under CARP, to address concerns on the collection of taxes. If warranted, request the presence of the Provincial Treasurer and Provincial Legal Officer to assist in such undertaking.
For the delinquent real property taxes with NDs already served, we recommend the management impose the legal remedies either by administrative auction thru levy on real property or judicial action, following the procedures authorized in the LGC, to enforce collection and to undertake the same expeditiously on a yearly basis to reduce amounts accumulated as receivables for delinquent taxes.

